foreignObject.div:
Formatters would be simple generic pieces of code to take
the results and pass then into a given viewer - this could
be done as the page is built when using something like php,
or it could be more dynamically using javascript

Does not need to define or limit the data structure of any
database behind a linked API, just the structure of the
expected inputs and the type and format of the results
A record of the actual value used in the search

A boolean value to indicate if the returned number of
results has been limited

The total number of possible results that could be returned
for a given search
A simple list of IIIF info.json URLs
A simple list of IIIF manifest URLs

A text description or comment related to the results,
specific to any given API

Simple keyword to act as the basis of a search - this could
be developed to allow phrases or simple AND and OR
combinations, but this would not be needed

the limit and from values are used to work with large sets
of results, and act as a limit on the number of results
returned for a given call and indicate where that number of
results should start from relative to the total number of
results
